    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The accepted answer builds two <code>LocalDate</code> objects, which are quite expensive if you are reading lot of data.\nI use this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>  public static int getDaysBetween(DateTime earlier, DateTime later)\n  {\n    return (int) TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toDays(later.getMillis()- earlier.getMillis());\n  }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>By calling <code>getMillis()</code> you use already existing variables.<br>\n<code>MILLISECONDS.toDays()</code> then, uses a simple arithmetic calculation, does not create any object.</p>\n"
  }, {
